Source-level summary
--------------------
In quivilib/model/image/freeimage.py:

    self._animation_scale_cache = {}

    ...

    cache_key = (width, height, scaling_filter)
    img = self._animation_scale_cache.get(cache_key)
    if img is not None:
        try:
            img.index = self.img.index
        except Exception:
            pass
    if img is None:
        img = self.img.rescale(width, height, scaling_filter)
        self._animation_scale_cache[cache_key] = img

    ...

    self._animation_scale_cache = {}

Behavior change
---------------
- Animated scaled views are cached by width, height, and scaling filter.
- Returning to a previously used zoom/fit size reuses the already-preloaded
  scaled AnimatedImage wrapper.
- The cached wrapper's frame index is synced to the source animation before use,
  so switching views does not jump back to an old frame.
- The cache is cleared on rotation because the source frame dimensions/content
  change.
- Static images are unaffected.

